sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects instances of svchost.exe running with an unusual or uncommon command line parameter by excluding known legitimate or common patterns.
This could point at a file masquerading as svchost, a process injection, or hollowing of a legitimate svchost instance.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: System Control Panel Item Loaded From Uncommon Location
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects image load events of system control panel items (.cpl) from uncommon or non-system locations which might be the result of sideloading.
Detects modification of autostart extensibility point (ASEP) in registry.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Victor Sergeev, Daniil Yugoslavskiy, Gleb Sukhodolskiy, Timur Zinniatullin, oscd.community, Tim Shelton, frack113 (split)

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects non-interactive PowerShell activity by looking at the "powershell" process with a non-user GUI process such as "explorer.exe" as a parent.

crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Detects suspicious single byte XORed keyword 'Mozilla/5.0' - it uses yara's XOR modifier and therefore cannot print the XOR key. You can use the CyberChef recipe linked in the reference field to brute force the used key.
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Florian Roth

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The analyzed sample is a sophisticated Trojan with Clipper and Backdoor capabilities. It uses significant obfuscation, including a custom XOR-based string decryption routine (sub_140001ad4) and dynamic API resolution to hinder static analysis. Key malicious behaviors include: 1. Clipboard Hijacking: The function sub_140001840 runs a persistent loop that identifies cryptocurrency wallet addresses (sub_140001274) and likely replaces them, a hallmark of Clipper malware. 2. Command and Control (C2) Communication: The binary establishes network connections via Winsock (sub_140002ff4) to a remote host, performing periodic beaconing (sub_14000414c) and system information gathering (sub_140004ab0). 3. Code Execution: It supports downloading additional payloads (sub_14000362c) and executing commands (sub_1400037f4) received from the C2 server. 4. Advanced Evasion: Function sub_140001dcc performs manual PE mapping or process hollowing techniques by using MapViewOfFile and VirtualProtect to change memory permissions (PAGE_EXECUTE_READWRITE) and compare memory segments against file views. Relevant IOCs include SHA256 eba62624838ce914ac259081ebf6d4d9c4c41b8cb499a4fe2dade0224a44e37a and obfuscated strings like 'hnxo./3yqq' and 'SMJMJAP\n@HH'.
